title: Megawati Respons Surya Paloh Soal Omongan Partai Sombong, Ini Penjelasannya
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV  Akhirnya Megawati Soekarnoputri menjawab terkait sindiran soal partai sombong yang sempat dilontarkan Ketum Partai Nasdem Surya Paloh.||||Ketua Umum PDIP menegaskan dirinya tak pernah menjelek-jelekkan partai politik mana pun.||||"Karena ada juga yang mengatakan 'ada sebuah partai sombong sekali'. Lah piye, kok dibilang sombong, emangnya kenapa,"kata Megawati.||||Megawati juga menegaskan tidak pernah menjelekkan partai mana pun. ||||Baca Juga Megawati Jengkel Dibilang Retak dengan Jokowi: Ngamuk Ajah Gak Pernah! di https://www.kompas.tv/article/301257/megawati-jengkel-dibilang-retak-dengan-jokowi-ngamuk-ajah-gak-pernah||||"Tidak pernah menjelekkan ketua apa pun. Saya berjalan sendiri membentuk partai saya yang saya hormati dan sayangi yang bernama Partai Demokrasi Indonesia Perjuangan. Jangan, jangan, negeri ini harus dibangun dengan bersatu," imbuhnya.||||Sebelumnya perihal partai sombong pernah disampaikan Surya Paloh saat penutupan Rakernas NasDem di JCC, Jakarta.||||"Kami menjaga komunikasi kepada seluruh komponen masyarakat secara lebih bijak, secara lebih luwes. Jadi buang itu praktik kesombongan, merasa hebat sendiri, merasa paling mantap sendiri, itu bukan NasDem. Ada urusan apa? Tapi kalau ada yang bersalah sangka kepada kami, maka kami harus arif dan bijaksana. NasDem masih banyak stok senyumnya. dan berpolitik dengan sukaria," kata Surya Paloh, Jumat (17/6/2022).||||Video Editor: Vila Randita|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/301270/megawati-respons-surya-paloh-soal-omongan-partai-sombong-ini-penjelasannya

title: US ban on imports from China's Xinjiang takes effect
description: A US ban on all imports of goods made in China's Xinjiang region is due to come into force today. ||It is a major exporter of cotton and tomatoes, but is also where Uighurs and other Muslim groups are being held in detention camps.||There are concerns that it could cause further problems to the global supply chain.||The ban intensifies pressure on Beijing over allegations of rights violations that took place at Xinjiang region against Muslim Uyghur and other minorities. ||China denies the claims and has warned of retaliatory measures.||||Al Jazeera‚Äôs Katrina Yu reports from Beijing, China.||||- Subscribe to our channel: http://aje.io/AJSubscribe ||- Follow us on Twitter: https://twitter.com/AJEnglish ||- Find us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/aljazeera ||- Check our website: https://www.aljazeera.com/||||#USChinaTensions #XinjiangBan #Uighurs

title: Zelenskyy calls Russia 'an evil to be defeated in battle' as seized areas get 'Russified' | DW News
description: As the war in Ukraine enters its fourth month, President Volodymyr Zelenskyy is dispelling hopes of negotiations with Russia anytime soon. In his latest video address, Zelenskyy called Russia's aggression an evil that can be contained only on the battlefield.  |Ukraine says Russia is stepping up its attacks in the eastern Donbas region, with Ukrainian troops doing 'everything possible' to hold their ground. Authorities said Russia's advantage in arms and equipment was making the situation very difficult. But in his nightly address on Monday, Zelenskyy remained defiant. |Meanwhile, Russia is tightening its grip on the occupied regions of Ukraine ‚Äî a sign that it has no intention of relinquishing control of these areas.  |Moscow has launch infrastructure projects in eastern Ukraine and is also attempting to "Russify" the population in occupied regions: It has been handing out Russian passports and introduced the ruble as the official currency. It's also changed the telephone country code and is broadcasting Russian television. |#Ukraine #Russia #War |Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/user/deutschewelleenglish?sub_confirmation=1|For more news go to: http://www.dw.com/en/|Follow DW on social media:|‚ñ∫Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/deutschewellenews/|‚ñ∫Twitter: https://twitter.com/dwnews|‚ñ∫Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/dwnews|F√ºr Videos in deutscher Sprache besuchen Sie: https://www.youtube.com/dwdeutsch

title: U.S, UK back India to block Pak's bid to list Indian national as global terrorist at UN
description: Big global embarrassment for Pakistan at the United Nations Security Council. India has foiled Pakistan's attempt to designate Indian national Gobinda Patnaik Duggivalasa as 'global terrorist'. Pakistan claimed that Duggivalasa was behind in several terrorists attacks in the country. India with the help of three permanent members of UNSC, U.S, UK, France and Albania, which is the President of the Council for this month, blocked Pakistan's bid. title: New details revealed in murder of Filipino lawyer in Philadelphia
description: The mother of a Filipino lawyer is demanding justice after a shooting in Philadelphia left her son dead over the weekend.|It happened around 4 a.m. Saturday near 38th and Spruce streets. Officials say John Albert Laylo, 35, and his mother, Leah Laylo, were in an Uber on the way to Philadelphia International Airport. The pair had been in the city visiting family since June 9.|Leah Laylo soon found herself under a hail of bullets.|"I just heard the window on my right side shatter, and when I looked at my son, John, he was bleeding," she said.|Police say the gunman, who investigators believe was in a black vehicle, came up from behind and fired several rounds into the car. The gunman then pulled up on the driver's side of the car and fired additional gunshots.|John was shot in the head and died from his injuries Sunday. His mother was injured by glass fragments.|Sources tell Action News that investigators are reviewing video that may prove the shooter targeted the wrong car. Police sources also say the shooter may have been in a black Cadillac.|#philadelphia #shooting #philippines |READ MORE: https://6abc.com/john-albert-laylo-murder-philadelphia-pa-shooting-philippines-lawyer-killed-38th-spruce-street/11981806/

title: RMT General Secretary Mick Lynch Quizzed On Whether He's a Marxist Amid Biggest Rail Strike | GMB
description: Strike by over 50,000 railway workers across the UK in what RMT describes as the 'biggest dispute on the network since 1989'. Today's action is followed by two more walkouts this Thursday and Saturday. The union claims that Network Rail and the train operating companies have subjected their staff to 'multiyear pay freezes and plan to cut thousands of jobs which will make the railways unsafe'. RMT says that despite 'intense talks' with rail bosses, it has not been able to secure a pay proposal nor a guarantee of no compulsory redundancies. RMT General Secretary Mick Lynch says: ‚ÄúRail companies are making at least ¬£500m a year in profits, whilst fat cat rail bosses have been paid millions during the Covid-19 pandemic. title: Elite Nasdem Temui Anies Baswedan di Rumah Dinas Gubernur Jakarta
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV - Ketua Nasdem Aceh Teuku Taufiqulhadi menyatakan bahwa dirinya termasuk yang merekomendasikan Gubernur Jakarta Anies Baswedan sebagai calon presiden.||||Hal tersebut diungkapkannya sesudah bertemu Anies di Rumah Dinas Gubernur yang terletak di Menteng, Jakarta Pusat.||||Menurut Taufiqulhadi, Nasdem Aceh merekomendasikan Anies karena dukungan dari masyarakat.||||Dalam pertemuan tersebut, Taufiqulhadi menyebutkan Anies kembali berterima kasih kepada Ketua Umum Nasdem Surya Paloh karena telah memberikannya kesempatan ikut berkompetisi dalam pertarungan kursi calon presiden.|||| ||||----||||Jangan lewatkan live streaming Kompas TV 24 jam non stop di https://www.kompas.tv/live||||Agar tidak ketinggalan berita-berita terkini, terlengkap, serta laporan langsung dari berbagai daerah di Indonesia. title: See Why Japan is the Most Disciplined Team in Volleyball History !!!
description: See Why Japan is the Most Disciplined Team in Volleyball History !!! Men's volleyball team Japan is currently one of the best teams in the volleyball nations league 2022. In this video you can see why japan is one of the most disciplined teams in the world. Japan is a team that fights and never gives up, and that can be seen in their incredible defense. It remains to be seen how this great team will perform in the upcoming part of the Men's VNL 2022.|The Japan men's national volleyball team represents Japan in international volleyball competitions and friendly matches. Their nickname is "RYUJIN NIPPON (ÈæçÁ•û NIPPON) ", meaning "Japanese Dragon God" or "Dragon God of Japan" in Japanese. Japan won a bronze medal at the Tokyo 1964 Olympic Games, followed by silver at Mexico 1968 and a gold at Munich 1972. The years after this have been less successful. Japan missed three successive Olympic Games before returning at Beijing 2008, where they failed to win a match. Japan then failed to qualify for the London 2012 Olympic Games and also missed Rio 2016 after finishing seventh at the World Olympic Qualification Tournament in Tokyo.|They also failed to qualify for the 2014 FIVB World Championship the first edition they had missed in 54 years. They had previously won FIVB World Championship bronze medals in 1970 and 1974. Japan silver medalists at the 1969 and 1977 World Cup. Japan has been less successful in the World League era. title: Momen Ganjar dan Bambang Pacul Salam Komando Disorak Para Kader di Acara Rakernas
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV  - PDIP menggelar rakernas bersama para kader untuk mendengarkan arahan Ketum Megawati Soekarnoputri. ||||Sebelum acara dimulai etua Badan Pemenangan Pemilu (Bappilu) PDIP Bambang Wuryanto atau akrab disapa Bambang Pacul menyapa para kader di ruangan. ||||Tiba Bambang ke arah depan dekat dengan posisi Ganjar Pranowo. ||||Sontak Ganjar pun berdiri menyodorkan tangan lebih dulu untuk bersalaman dengan Bambang Pacul.||||Baca Juga Tanggapan Ganjar Atas Pernyataan Bambang Pacul di https://www.kompas.tv/article/221200/tanggapan-ganjar-atas-pernyataan-bambang-pacul||||Tak lama setelah itu keduanya kembali bersalaman hingga menyambut sorak pada kader lainnya. ||||Sebelumnya  Bambang Pacul kerap melontarkan kritikan terhadap Ganjar Pranowo.||||Elektabilitas Ganjar di sejumlah lembaga survei pun juga sering disebut-sebut menjadi nama kuat untuk Capres 2024 ketimbang nama Puan Maharani. ||||Video Editor: Vila Randita|| ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/301133/momen-ganjar-dan-bambang-pacul-salaman-disorak-para-kader-di-acara-rakernas

title: Momen Jokowi Tertawa Dengar Cerita Lucu Megawati di Raker PDIP soal Teriak Merdeka
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS TV  Presiden Joko Widodo atau Jokowi tertawa mendengar cerita lucu Ketua Umum Megawati Soekarnoputri soal teriakan merdeka.||||Suasana tersebut nampak saat Megawati membuka Rakernas PDIP, Selasa (21/6).||||"Pak Jokowi supaya tahu, kemarin saya diundang untuk memberikan arahan di Angkatan Laut. Supaya bapak Presiden tahu, itu ketika saya teriak-teriak merdeka, media-media dan banyak orang 'udah merdeka kok terus teriak-teriak merdeka?'" kisah Mega pada Jokowi.||||Baca Juga Presiden Jokowi Hadiri Rakernas PDIP di https://www.kompas.tv/article/301098/presiden-jokowi-hadiri-rakernas-pdip||||"Jadi saya bilang, ya itu maunya saya. Tapi untuk mengingatkan, meski kita telah merdeka, bukan berarti kita lupa kita orang yang bebas dan berdaulat," lanjut Mega diiringi tepuk tangan hadirin.||||Lalu Megawati bercerita momen-momen saat dia mengajak prajurit AL berteriak merdeka, dan hanya sedikit yang mengikutinya.||||"Waktu saya teriak merdeka, hanya berapa orang. Saya bilang kurang,"||||"Saya merdeka lagi, agak banyak. Jangan lupa, saya ini pernah panglima tertinggi.," kata Megawati disambut tawa tamu Rakernas PDIP termasuk Presiden Jokowi.||||Baca Juga Megawati Resmikan Kapal Perang Bernama KRI Bung Karno di https://www.kompas.tv/article/300986/megawati-resmikan-kapal-perang-bernama-kri-bung-karno||||Kisah lucu tersebut disampaikan Megawati kala dirinya berbicara membuka Rakernas PDIP yang digelar Selasa (21/6).||||Sejumlah petinggi PDIP hadir, termasuk ketua DPP PDIP Puan Maharani yang duduk di samping Presiden Jokowi.||||Video Editor: Laurensius Galih||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/301136/momen-jokowi-tertawa-dengar-cerita-lucu-megawati-di-raker-pdip-soal-teriak-merdeka

title: Food crisis: EU lashes out at Russia; Moscow blasts West's 'destructive' grain stance | WION

title: ‚ÄòSelective Religiophobia‚Äô: India calls out Kabul Gurdwara ‚Äòhate crime‚Äô at UN
description: In a strong worded statement on the Kabul Gurdwara attack, India called out selectivism in condemning hatred against non-abrahamic religions at the United Nations. Speaking at the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA), India's Permanent Representative of India to the United Nations, Ambassador TS Tirumurti raised concerns about the 'selective' efforts to combat religiophobias. "And on 18th June, a couple of days ago and on the very day we commemorated the International Day for countering hate speech, we saw yet another tragic example of this against Sikh religion, this time in Kabul, Afghanistan. The Gurudwara Karte Parwan was attacked, desecrated and damaged. We condemn in the strongest terms this cowardly dastardly attack where lives were tragically lost," said Tirumurti at the informal High-Level Meeting to mark the commemoration of the first International Day for Countering Hate Speech. Watch this video for more details.|#kabulattack #india #unga #tstirumurti #hate #religiophobia #unitednations #kabulgurdwara #afghanistan #√≠sis #terrorist #terrorism #kabul

title: A National Trend Comes To Fishers, Indiana: Big Companies Buying Up Single-Family Homes
description: Fishers, Indiana ‚Äì named by Money Magazine as one of the best places to live ‚Äì is part of a national trend: real estate investment groups buying up houses and renting them out, in some cases to families who had dreamed of owning their own homes. NBC News‚Äô Antonia Hylton meets the Collier family, who rented a home nearby while trying to save up for their own. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs becoming more and more challenging to even get out of the renting game,‚Äù John Collier says. The mayor says that it‚Äôs ‚Äúvery, very difficult‚Äù to communicate with these companies that are buying up hundreds of houses in his community. In a statement, the National Rental Home Council says that its "member companies own just a fraction of the homes throughout the state of Indiana.‚Äù Proponents say these rental companies are creating opportunities for families to live in homes they might not otherwise be able to afford to buy, including traditional houses with yards.|¬ª Subscribe to NBC News: http://nbcnews.to/SubscribeToNBC|¬ª Watch more NBC video: http://bit.ly/MoreNBCNews|NBC News Digital is a collection of innovative and powerful news brands that deliver compelling, diverse and engaging news stories. title: Remembering longtime NewsHour political analyst Mark Shields
description: Mark Shields, a syndicated columnist and commentator, was a fixture on the NewsHour for 33 years, providing insights into our nation's politics each Friday night before his retirement in December 2020. He died on Saturday at the age of 85. title: Biden Considering Federal Gas Tax Holiday
description: President Biden says he is considering a federal gas tax holiday, which could save consumers just over 18 cents a gallon. The proposal would offer a small, temporary savings as the national average price of gas hovers near $5 a gallon, according to AAA. A handful of states already suspended taxes for several weeks this spring. title: Bodycam Shows Florida Police Shoot Convicted Felon During Traffic Stop
description: The Indian River County Sheriff's Office in Florida released bodycam footage showing police shooting a convicted felon during a traffic stop. Police say they began shooting when the suspect allegedly armed himself and fled the scene. title: Nova Scotia mass shooting: Video shows the moment RCMP officers killed gunman Gabriel Wortman
description: WARNING: Video contains disturbing content and is not suitable for all viewers. Viewer discretion is advised.|Videos of Nova Scotia RCMP officers fatally shooting the perpetrator of one of the worst mass killings in Canadian history have been released to the public.|The decision Monday from the commissioners of a public inquiry into the 2020 Nova Scotia mass shooting reversed their previous decision to shield the videos from publication.|The five videos from various security cameras at an Irving Big Stop gas station in Enfield, N.S., were recorded when RCMP officers killed the gunman on April 19, 2020, ending a 13-hour rampage that claimed 22 lives.|For more info, please go to https://globalnews.ca/news/8934174/videos-rcmp-killing-ns-shooter-released/|Subscribe to Global News Channel HERE: http://bit.ly/20fcXDc|Like Global News on Facebook HERE: http://bit.ly/255GMJQ|Follow Global News on Twitter HERE: http://bit.ly/1Toz8mt|Follow Global News on Instagram HERE: https://bit.ly/2QZaZIB|#GlobalNews #novascotia #novascotiashooting #nsshooting #rcmp #mcc

title: Trump Criminal Charges? Majority Of Americans Say He Should Be Indicted And Not Just Democrats
description: After evidence presented by the Jan. 6 committee during its public hearings showed Donald Trump knew he lost the election and still tried to steal it, nearly 60 percent of Americans believe Trump should be criminally charged, according to an ABC News/Ipsos poll. In a major shift, the number of Republicans who think Trump is criminally liable has roughly doubled from April to June. title: President Joe Biden considers federal gas tax holiday to reduce prices
description: President Joe Biden is considering a federal gas tax holiday to reduce prices.  Right now, drivers in Metro Detroit are paying an average of $5.26 per gallon.  Suspending the federal gas tax would drop prices by about 18 cents per gallon, putting prices at around $5.08, which is still pretty high but is better for the consumer.

title: Prime Time With Ravish Kumar: Army Begins Agniveer Hiring Process
description: Prime Time With Ravish Kumar - June 20, 2022: The Indian Army today issued a notification that the registration under the 'Agnipath' military defence scheme will start next month. The 'Agnipath' scheme, which was unveiled by the government last week, aims to bring in men and women between the ages of 17-and-a-half and 21 into the armed forces for a four-year tenure. The BJP has come under fire with hundreds of potential recruits protesting against the shorter tenure. Amid the rising demands for the scrapping of the newly launched Agnipath recruitment scheme for the military, a senior Army officer on Sunday clarified that the programme will not be rolled back. title: Kyrie Irving & Nets reach impasse, Lakers & Knicks rumored to be interested | NBA | UNDISPUTED

title: Modi Govt's 'Agnipath' gets Corporate India's support; Tata Sons, Biocon, Goenkas back scheme
description: After Anand Mahindra, N Chandrasekaran, the Tata Sons Chairman, backed Modi government's Agnipath scheme amid protests. He said Agnipath will make available a very disciplined youth for the industry, including the Tata Group. Harsh Goenka, chairman of Rama Prasad Goenka Group, also spoke in support of Agnipath. Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw, Executive Chairperson of Biocon Ltd, also lent her support to the scheme. Earlier, industrialist Anand Mahindra made an offer to employ 'Agniveers' in the Mahindra group. title: We Had to Fire Onyx!
description: We Had to Fire Onyx! Our last day of planting in 2022 and Onyx got the land roller stuck. |A PARTY LIKE NO OTHER! Join us July 1st, 2022 in Alexandria, MN to Celebrate 1 Million Subscribers (hopefully), enjoy some great music and contribute to a great cause! We're teaming up with Anderson Bash to kick off our Grain Bin Safety Campaign again! The goal of this campaign is to reduce the occurrence of grain bin accidents by raising awareness of the hazards and by raising funds to equip first responders with the tools and training needed to respond quickly when necessary in the event of a grain bin accident. title: President Macron loses majority in split French vote - BBC News
description: President Emmanuel Macron has lost control of the French National Assembly following a strong performance by a left alliance and the far right in the elections.|His centrist coalition lost dozens of seats in an election that has left French politics fragmented.|The prime minister he had only recently appointed, Elisabeth Borne, said the situation was unprecedented.|"This situation represents a risk for our country, given the risks we're facing nationally and internationally," she said. "We will work as of tomorrow to build a working majority."|Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|#BBCNews

title: Ukrainian forces break Russian troops' first line of defence in Kherson region
description: Ukraine appears to be making inroads against Russia in the south. A local official said troops have broken through the first line of defence in the largely occupied Kherson region. Large swathes of territory in the key gateway to Crimea were seized by Russian troops early in Moscow‚Äôs invasion. title: Why Mercedes is in a major F1 conflict with Ferrari and Red Bull
description: Mercedes has barely troubled Ferrari and Red Bull in Formula 1 this season but is now in conflict with them off-track in a BIG way. |The world champion team was at the heart of a huge argument over the Canadian Grand Prix weekend, after the FIA made an initial attempt to intervene in the dispute over the porpoising and bottoming out suffered by the 2022 cars. |Ferrari and Red Bull have pushed back against a last-minute and then quickly-postponed technical directive issued on the eve of the Montreal event, prompting Mercedes boss Toto Wolff to label the political games ‚Äúpitiful‚Äù. |Suddenly, a topic that was only bubbling away in the background until recently, is now one of the most controversial stories of the season - and one that looks far from settled. |#F1 #Mercedes #CanadianGP |READ MORE HERE|https://the-race.com/formula-1/ferrari-challenges-validity-of-fias-action-on-f1-bouncing/|Subscribe: http://the-race.com/youtube_subscribe|Website: http://the-race.com/|Twitter: @wearetherace|Instagram: @wearetherace|Facebook: http://facebook.com/wearetherace|Podcasts: http://the-race.com/podcasts|Thanks for watching - please like, share and comment, please also hit subscribe to show your support so we'll keep doing what we're doing.|https://www.the-race.com|http://www.twitter.com/wearetherace

title: Australia bonds with India amid China threat; Dy PM in New Delhi with security cooperation agenda
description: Australia‚Äôs Deputy Prime Minister and Defence Minister Richard Marles embarks on a four-day visit to India, aimed at bolstering defence and security cooperation between the two countries. Marles, who is the first senior member of the Anthony Albanese government to travel to New Delhi, will meet Union defence minister Rajnath Singh, external affairs minister S Jaishankar and other senior Indian officials. His visit to India comes less than a month after the formation of the new government in Australia, highlighting the importance of its ties with India. Both countries currently have strained ties with China. title: Ahilya Senses A Danger | Punyashlok Ahilyabai | Mon - Fri At 7:30 pm

title: PM Modi defends 'unpleasant reforms' amid Agnipath protests; 'Nation will benefit...'
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Monday said many decisions and reforms may seem unpleasant but the entire country will experience the benefits of it. The prime minister didn't name the protests which continue across the country against Agnipath, the recruitment scheme for the armed forces. The Centre has made it clear that the scheme will not be rolled back. title: Building 21st century road network to power India's development
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi laid the foundation stone of two sections of the Bengaluru Ring Road project.  The project to be developed at a cost of more than Rs 2280 crore will help reduce traffic congestion in the city. Prime Minister also laid the foundation stone of various other road projects : six laning of Nelamangala-Tumkur section of NH-48; widening of Punjalkatte-Charmadi section of NH-73; rehabilitation and upgradation of a section of NH-69. The cumulative cost to be incurred in these projects is about Rs 3150 crore. Prime Minister laid the foundation stone of Multi Modal Logistics Park, which is being developed at Muddalinganahalli, about 40 km from Bengaluru at a cost of about Rs 1800 crore. title: Sch√∂ne, tote Ostsee: Das Dorschsterben und die Folgen | Doku | NDR | 45 Min
description: Jahrzehntelang hat die Wissenschaft davor gewarnt: Vor zwei Jahren ist der Bestand an Dorsch in der Ostsee komplett zusammengebrochen. Und daran ist nicht nur die √úberfischung schuld. Was in der Ostsee genau passiert ist, ist nun  wissenschaftlich belegt. 45 Min-Autor Carsten Rau hat Forschende mit der Kamera begleitet und fragt in seiner Doku auch, was das Fehlen des Dorsches f√ºr die Betriebe und Menschen an der Ostseek√ºste bedeutet.¬† ||||**************************||Bild-Credit: picture alliance/dpa/dpa-Zentralbild | Fotograf: Bernd W√ºstneck||**************************|| ||Aktuelle Studie: Klimawandel und √úberd√ºngung sch√§digen Dorschbestand|| ||Eine wesentliche Rolle dabei, dass die Dorschbest√§nde zusammengebrochen sind, spielen der Klimawandel und die √úberd√ºngung durch die Landwirtschaft. Das haben Wissenschaftler:innen des Th√ºnen-Instituts f√ºr Ostseefischerei in einem Forschungsprojekt herausgefunden, dessen erste Ergebnisse dem NDR exklusiv vorliegen. Der NDR hat die Forschung f√ºr die Studie, die im kommenden Jahr ver√∂ffentlicht wird, √ºber mehrere Monate begleitet. || ||Zu wenig Sauerstoff und zu viel W√§rme f√ºr den Dorsch|| ||"Wir waren sehr √ºberrascht, dass sich w√§hrend der Sommermonate sauerstoffarmes Wasser vom Grund der Ostsee bis weit in die h√∂heren Schichten ausbreitet", sagt Dr. Uwe Krumme vom Th√ºnen-Institut. "Dort trifft es direkt auf die stark erw√§rmten Wasserschichten. Wo das passiert, ist kein Habitat mehr f√ºr Dorsche" - also kein Raum mehr, in dem diese Fische √ºberleben k√∂nnen.|| ||Zehn Monate lang hat das Institut in einem f√ºnf Quadratkilometer gro√üen Forschungsfeld in der Mecklenburger Bucht Umweltdaten wie Sauerstoff- und Salzgehalt sowie die Temperatur des Wassers aufgezeichnet. Dazu hatten die Forschenden insgesamt 30 Messstationen am Meeresgrund verankert. Dieses Projekt in Zusammenarbeit mit dem Leibnitz-Institut f√ºr Ostseeforschung ist bisher einzigartig in der Westlichen Ostsee.¬†|| ||"Die neuen Daten sind √§u√üerst beunruhigend", so Dr. Krumme. "Und wir werden √ºberpr√ºfen, ob dieses Ph√§nomen auch in anderen Teilen der Westlichen Ostsee zu beobachten ist."|| ||Fischer: "Ohne Dorsch k√∂nnen wir nichts verdienen"|| ||Der Verlust der Dorsche bedeutet f√ºr viele Betriebe und Menschen ein wirtschaftliches Desaster. Kapit√§n Andr√© Hamann hat sein Leben lang Dorsche in der Ostsee gefischt, so wie sein Vater und Gro√üvater vor ihm. Jetzt steht er im Steuerhaus seines Stahlkutters "Westbank" und f√§hrt das modern ausger√ºstete 20-Meter-Schiff zum Verschrotten Richtung D√§nemark. "Ohne Dorsch k√∂nnen wir nichts verdienen. F√ºr andere Fischarten wie Flundern gibt es nicht genug Geld. Damit k√∂nnten wir nicht mal unseren Treibstoff bezahlen!" Die "Westbank" war einer der letzten gro√üen Schleppnetzkutter der Ostsee. Und Kapit√§n Hamann hat keine Ahnung, was aus ihm mit Mitte 40 werden soll.|| ||Zu viel Fisch f√ºr Kormorane und Kegelrobben?|| ||In der Haifischbar auf Fehmarn sitzen die Fischer, Gastwirte und Kapit√§ne des Hafens von Burgstaaken zusammen und haben eine ganz andere Erkl√§rung: "Es gibt hier doch kaum mehr Kutter und Fischer, die Fangquoten werden seit Jahren drastisch gesenkt", sagt einer der M√§nner. "Aber die Kormorane und die Kegelrobben, die werden st√§ndig mehr und fressen jeden Tag tonnenweise Fisch! Und von der Politik werden die auch noch gesch√ºtzt!"|| ||Die 45 Min-Reportage beschreibt in eindrucksvollen Bildern die dramatische Lage an der deutschen Ostseek√ºste zwischen L√ºbeck und R√ºgen. Und sie gibt seltene Einblicke in das Leben der betroffenen Menschen, die sehr offen Stellung beziehen. Dabei fragt Autor Carsten Rau, selbst Angler, auch nach der eigenen Verantwortung f√ºr das Verschwinden der Dorsche. Hierdurch verlieren viele nicht nur ihr Einkommen, sondern auch ihren Lebensinhalt als Menschen der K√ºste.||||Mehr Infos hier: ||https://www.ndr.de/fernsehen/sendungen/45_min/Schoene-tote-Ostsee-Das-Dorschsterben-und-die-Folgen,sendung1249608.html

title: Euphoria Cinematography Breakdown ‚Äî DP Marcell R√©v on Lighting, Camera Movement, and Oners
description: Euphoria cinematography breakdown ‚Äî a look at how the cinematography in Euphoria is designed to capture ‚Äúemotional realism" according to cinematographer Marcell Rev.|Euphoria Cinematography Breakdown ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ https://bit.ly/ct-eu|StudioBinder Blog ‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ http://bit.ly/sb-bl|‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ|Chapters:|00:00 - Intro to Euphoria's Cinematography|00:37 - Capturing Emotional Realism|01:16 - Dynamic Lighting|04:08 - Camera Movement|06:03 - Long Takes|08:27 - Takeaways|‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ|Euphoria Cinematography Breakdown|If there‚Äôs one aspect that stands out with HBO‚Äôs Euphoria, it‚Äôs the imagery. From the lighting, camera movement, and long takes, everything about Euphoria‚Äôs cinematography is designed to capture ‚Äúemotional realism.‚Äù In this video, we‚Äôre going to look inside these elements to see just how this is achieved.|Euphoria Cinematography Lighting|The lighting in Euphoria is both dynamic and colorful, intended to highlight the heightened emotions of the characters. Most of the time, bold primary colors are used. And in some cases, the mixing of colors enhances the effect. For example, nighttime lighting blends blueish moonlight with warm yellow tungsten streetlights. And during the second season, the decision was made to shoot on film, which further enhanced the color palettes. That‚Äôs why the cinematography of Euphoria Season 2 looks so different from the first season.|Euphoria Cinematography Camera Movement|Camera movement is also a huge part of the overall Euphoria cinematography. As cinematographer Marcell R√©v explains, the moving camera brought a certain energy that ties the different storylines together. Not only is the camera as active as the characters, but it also brings us directly into their mental state. Consider the moment in the pilot as the hallway literally spins around Rue as she experiences an ‚Äúaltered state.‚Äù|Euphoria Cinematography Long Takes|The final key element bringing all of the Euphoria cinematography together is the use of long takes. Often these long takes move in and out of rooms, connecting characters in a single shot and creating unity between all of their experiences. The biggest set-piece is the now-iconic carnival scene where dollys, cranes, and Steadicams were used to capture the spectacle all in ‚Äúoner.‚Äù|What filmmakers like Sam Levinson and Marcell R√©v have made is a loud and vibrant ode to the chaos of youth. Euphoria cinematography is defined as big and bold but it‚Äôs not done for its own sake. title: Russia rains rockets on Ukraine positions | BM-27 Uragan destroys Ukrainian military equipment
description: Russian troops launched a massive assault on Ukraine positions by raining rockets from BM-27 URAGAN. title: Hati-Hati, Penipuan Modus Baru yang Bisa Menguras Rekeningmu dalam 5 Menit!
description: KOMPAS.TV-Awas modus begal rekening yang bisa menguras rekening dalam 5 menit.||||Teknologi yang semakin maju terkadang juga memberi dampak buruk bagi masyarakat.||||Contohnya seperti yang sedang marak saat ini, yakni penipuan dengan modus social engineering atau soceng.||||Si penipu berpura-pura menjadi petugas bank, namun bertanya password, PIN, MPIN, OTP, atau data pribadi.||||Bahkan mereka bisa menghubungi korban melalui akun email, website bank, telepon, dan akun media sosial.||||Otoritas Jasa Keuangan (OJK) mengimbau masyarakat, untuk waspada terhadap penipuan bermodus soceng ini.||||Melansir akun instagram resmi Otoritas Jasa Keuangan. Berikut modus penipuan social engineering atau soceng yang harus kamu ketahui:||||Menawarkan Jadi Agen Laku Pandai||||Mereka tidak memberikan syarat yang rumit, dan meminta korban mentransfer uang untuk mendapat mesin EDC.||||Informasi Perubahan Biaya Transfer||||Penipu akan berpura-pura jadi petugas bank, lalu kamu akan diperintah mengisi tautan yang meminta data pribadi.||||Tawaran Nasabah Prioritas||||Pelaku akan berbohong dengan menawarkan iklan upgrade menjadi nasabah prioritas dengan rayuan manis berkedok promosi.||||Akun Layanan Konsumen Palsu||||Akun palsu ini muncul saat konsumen mengeluh mengenai layanan perbankan, kemudian penipu akan menawarkan bantuan, dengan mengarahkan ke website palsu yang meminta data pribadi.||||Baca Juga 4 Poin Penting Aturan Baru OJK: Debt Collector Tak Boleh Seenaknya, Ancaman Masuk Delik Pidana di https://www.kompas.tv/article/291792/4-poin-penting-aturan-baru-ojk-debt-collector-tak-boleh-seenaknya-ancaman-masuk-delik-pidana||||Editor Video & Grafis: Joshua Victor ||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/300975/hati-hati-penipuan-modus-baru-yang-bisa-menguras-rekeningmu-dalam-5-menit

title: Leftist Gustavo Petro wins Colombia's presidential election | DW News
description: Leftist presidential candidate Gustavo Petro wins Colombia's election by a narrow margin. The former guerilla and current senator will be Colombia's first leftist leader. He's edged out his opponent, former mayor and millionare Rodolfo Hernandez. Petro's win marks a drastic change in presidential politics for a country that has long marginalized the left for its perceived association with decades of insurgency.|Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/user/deutschewelleenglish?sub_confirmation=1|For more news go to: http://www.dw.com/en/|Follow DW on social media:|‚ñ∫Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/deutschewellenews/|‚ñ∫Twitter: https://twitter.com/dwnews|‚ñ∫Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/dwnews|F√ºr Videos in deutscher Sprache besuchen Sie: https://www.youtube.com/dwdeutsch|#Colombia #GustavoPetro #RodolfoHernandez

title: EXPOSED: The shocking lengths truck drivers take to meet deadlines | 60 Minutes Australia
description: Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | Highway to Hell (2005)|If you're like us, just the thought of a huge semi looming up ahead on the highway is unnerving.  And there's every reason to be wary, even downright scared.  It's a fact that most truckies break the rules.  They speed, they're doped to the eyeballs, they drive till they drop. And their bosses not only allow this lawlessness, many expect it.  During the course of this investigation, we tailed one driver, who was at the wheel for 22 solid hours. That's illegal and so were the speeds he clocked up.  So you really have to ask how many more innocent people have to die before these blokes get the message.|WATCH more of 60 Minutes Australia: https://www.60minutes.com.au |LIKE 60 Minutes Australia on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/60Minutes9 |FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Twitter: https://twitter.com/60Mins |FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/60minutes9|For forty years, 60 Minutes have been telling Australians the world‚Äôs greatest stories. title: CREATIVE NAIL DESIGNS YOU CAN MAKE AT HOME
description: Hello, crafty girls! ||Today we have prepared a new video full of awesome ideas and tricky hacks for the best manicure. Some nail designs are really mind-blowing. For example, we will show you how to make a baby hair brush on your nail. WOW! Sounds amazing and very unusual! But you need long nails to repeat this design. We will also show you different designs that are suitable for short nails. It is possible to make a stunning pattern using a plastic bag, just put a few drops of colored nail polish, mix them with a plastic bag and spread over the nail. They find out their identities with the help of their parents. The police try to find the cause behind the crime and they suspect two guys who were hanging out with the girls. What could be the motive behind the crime? Are the suspects the real convicts or is there a master mind behind this whole crime? What will happen next? Watch the episode now to know more.|Show Name: Crime Patrol 2.0|Episode: 13 - 23 March 2022|Producer: Anup Soni, Shamael Khan|#CrimePatrol2.0 #CP2.0 #‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§á‡§Æ‡§™‡•à‡§ü‡•ç‡§∞‡•â‡§≤2.0  #SETindia|About Crime Patrol 2.0:|--------------------------------|Crime Patrol 2.0 is the New Crime Patrol series wherein our objective is to tell our viewers about the crime which happen/May happen around them. One of the data suggests most of the crime which happens in our country is done by people whom the victims already knew and our purpose is to depict those stories where crime has been done by someone close to the victim. Our show communicates the message to be aware of the surroundings we live in so that we do not fall prey to such evil-minded people.| Two Innocents | Crime Patrol 2.0 - Ep 13 | Full Episode | 23 March 2022

title: Penampakan Spanduk Foto Anies Baswedan Bareng Presiden RI yang Dicopot Satpol PP
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS.TV - Inilah spanduk yang dibentangkan di atas Jembatan Penyebrangan Orang (JPO) di Pulogadung, Jakarta Timur.||||Nampak di spanduk tersebut menampilkan foto Gubernur DKI Jakarta Anies Baswedan yang disandingkan bersama foto seluruh Presiden Republik Indonesia.||||Foto Anies Baswedan terlihat berada diurutan ke delapan tepatnya disamping foto presiden Jokowi.||||Baca Juga Ini 3 Nama Diusulkan Nasdem jadi Capres 2024: Anies, Andika Perkasa, Ganjar di https://www.kompas.tv/article/300232/ini-3-nama-diusulkan-nasdem-jadi-capres-2024-anies-andika-perkasa-ganjar||||Belum diketahui siapa yang memasang spanduk tersebut. Namun diduga spanduk ini baru dipasang lantaran warna spanduk belum kusam.||||Sementara itu, petugas Satpol PP Kelurahan Rawamangun yang tiba di lokasi langsung melakukan penertiban dengan mencopot spanduk tersebut.||||Penertiban dilakukan karena tidak berizin dan melanggar perda DKI Jakarta nomor 8 tahun 2007 tentang ketertiban umum.||||Video Editor: Agung Ramdani||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/300834/penampakan-spanduk-foto-anies-baswedan-bareng-presiden-ri-yang-dicopot-satpol-pp

title: Putin's missiles destroy Command Centre in Dnipropetrovsk; Ukraine Generals 'killed' in strike
description: As many as 50 Ukrainian armed force officers and generals have reportedly been killed after Russia launched Kalibr missiles to destroy Western-supplied M777 howitzers and armoured vehicles. Putin's troops pounded a command centre in the eastern Ukraine's Dnipropetrovsk resulting in 'heavy casualties' for Ukrainians. Russia claims that its offensive against Severodonetsk was proceeding successfully after it took control of a district in the outskirts of the city. Moscow scaled aggression after the West supplied arms to war-torn Ukraine. Watch this report to know more.|#Russia #Ukraine #War #Putin #KalibrMissiles #Dnipropetrovsk #Severodonetsk #Zelensky

title: Big crackdown over 'Agnipath' violence as over 1,500 booked; Forces bar entry for 'arsonists'
description: Big crackdown by govt after violent protests across states over 'Agnipath' scheme. Over 1,500 protesters have been booked while hundreds of FIRs have been filed in several states. 805 people have been booked in Bihar, from where these protests started after the announcement of the scheme. The Ministry of Home Affairs have also banned 35 Whatsapp groups for spreading fake news over 'Agnipath'. The action comes as the defence ministry has declared that there is no place for 'arsonists' in the forces. Watch this report to know more.|#agnipath #agniveer #bharatbandh #protests #fir #fakenews #whatsapp #bihar #uttarpradesh #uttrakhand #telangana #secunderabad #mha #amitshah #modigovernment #defence #defenceforces #defenceministry

title: Watch: Cop, Wife On Scooter Swallowed By Drain On Waterlogged UP Road
description: A policeman and his wife escaped with injuries after their two-wheeler fell headlong into a drain inundated with rainwater in Uttar Pradesh's Aligarh. The cop, with his wife riding pillion, was going to a hospital in Aligarh. The video from the accident site shows the cop navigating the waterlogged road. The front wheel hits something, and the couple is catapulted into the drain water. title: Polisi Olah TKP Kasus Tewas Anggota Brimob di Jayawijaya, Diserang Usai Tembak Sapi
description: JAYAWIJAYA, KOMPAS.TV - Polres Jayawijaya melakukan olah tempat kejadian perkara (TKP) dengan menghadirkan saksi dalam kasus pembunuhan Bripda Diego Rumaropen, personel Brimob Yon D Wamena di Napua, Wamena, Kabupaten Jayawijaya.||||Dalam olah TKP ini polisi menghadirkan saksi pemilik sapi, pembeli sapi termasuk ketiga saksi lainya ada saat insiden tersebut.||||Hasil dari olah TKP ini polisi akan dikumpulkan dan dicocokan barang bukti dilokasi kejadian untuk ditingkatkan ke penyidik.||||Dalam penyelidikannya, polisi menduga pelaku pembacokan dan perampasan senjata api di lokasi kejadian berjumlah 2 orang.||||Baca Juga Polisi Gelar Olah TKP Kasus Tewasnya Anggota Brimob di Papua, 5 Saksi Dihadirkan di https://www.kompas.tv/article/300748/polisi-gelar-olah-tkp-kasus-tewasnya-anggota-brimob-di-papua-5-saksi-dihadirkan||||Berdasarkan kronologi yang diterima, menyebutkan korban bersama Danki Brimob Yon D Wamena, AKP R ditelepon oleh saudara AM untuk membantunya  menembak sapi milik AM di Napua.||||Kemudian, AKP R mengajak Bripda Diego Rumaropen ke lokasi kejadian. AKP R membawa 1 pucuk senjata api sniper styer dan bripda Diego membawa senjata api ak 101.||||Pukul 15.20 WIT, setelah sapi ditembak oleh AKP R, lalu AKP R menitip senjata api yang digunakan untuk menembak sapi ke Bripda Diego karena mau mengecek sapi tersebut.||||Sesaat setelah ditinggalkan AKP Rustam, korban didatangi 2 orang dengan menggunakan parang dan membacok Bripda Diego, lalu mengambil 2 pucuk senjata api dan melarikan diri.||||Atas peristiwa ini polisi terus mengejar pelaku pembunuhan dan perampasan 2 pucuk senjata.||||Video Editor: Agung Ramdani||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/300763/polisi-olah-tkp-kasus-tewas-anggota-brimob-di-jayawijaya-diserang-usai-tembak-sapi

title: Protesters detained in India after violent clash over new military recruitment scheme
description: Subscribe to our YouTube channel for free here: |https://sc.mp/subscribe-youtube|Protesters in India have clashed with police during rallies against a new military recruitment scheme. Dozens of people were detained on June 19, 2022, as police used batons and tear gas to disperse protesters who had taken to the streets and damaged government buildings to protest against the policy. The scheme announced June 14 calls for young adults to be admitted into the armed forces for a period of four years and 75 per cent of the recruits taken in from 2022 must retire after their terms with no pension benefits. The new plan is a major departure from the past when military service was usually seen as a lifetime job, and comes as the nation‚Äôs unemployment rate is at its worst level since the 1970s.|Related story:|Indian trains set ablaze in protests against military hiring changes https://sc.mp/mclj|Support us:|https://subscribe.scmp.com|Follow us on:|Website:  https://www.scmp.com|Facebook:  https://facebook.com/scmp|Twitter:  https://twitter.com/scmpnews|Instagram:  https://instagram.com/scmpnews|Linkedin:  https://www.linkedin.com/company/south-china-morning-post/|#scmp #Asia #India

title: Transgender swimmers banned from elite women‚Äôs races - BBC News
description: World swimming‚Äôs governing body has effectively banned transgender athletes from competing in women‚Äôs elite races.|FINA voted to stop any person who has transitioned from competing in the events, if they have been through any stage of male puberty.  |They are aiming to establish a new ‚Äúopen‚Äù category of competition for swimmers whose gender identity is different from their biological sex.|The new policy, which was passed with 71% of the vote of FINA members, was described as "only a first step towards full inclusion" for transgender athletes.|The former Great Britain swimmer Sharron Davies, who has argued against transgender participation in women's elite swimming, said she was "really proud of FINA".|However Athlete Ally, an LGBT advocacy group, called the new policy "discriminatory and harmful‚Äù. |Huw Edwards presents BBC News at Ten reporting by sports correspondent Jane Dougall. |Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|#BBCNews

description: Tyler tops buttery, braised Brussels sprouts with crispy Parmesan breadcrumbs!|Subscribe to #discoveryplus to stream more of #TylersUltimate: http://discoverypl.us/2NeKVgd. |Get the recipe ‚ñ∂ https://foodtv.com/3zD7Tnu|Subscribe to Food Network ‚ñ∂ http://foodtv.com/YouTube|Fried chicken, burgers, spaghetti and meatballs ‚Äì if you're going to have only one recipe for these crowd-pleasing classics, it might as well be the ultimate ‚Äì Tyler's Ultimate.|Welcome to Food Network, where learning to cook is as simple as clicking play! We'll give you a behind-the-scenes look at our best shows, take you inside our favorite restaurant and be your resource in the kitchen to make sure every meal is a 10/10!|Bacon-Braised Brussels Sprouts|RECIPE COURTESY OF TYLER FLORENCE|Level: Easy|Total: 50 min|Prep: 20 min|Cook: 30 min|Yield: 4 servings|Ingredients|1 1/2 pounds Brussels sprouts, washed and cut in half|4 ounces (about 1/2 cup) bacon, cut into small squares|1 clove garlic, peeled and smashed, plus 2 cloves, roughly chopped|4 sprigs thyme, plus 2 sprigs thyme, leaves only, chopped|2 cups low-sodium chicken stock|Kosher salt|Freshly ground black pepper|3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar|1/2 cup grated Parmigiano-Reggiano|1 cup panko bread crumbs|2 sprigs rosemary, leaves only, chopped|Extra-virgin olive oil|Directions|Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.|Take a large pan and set over medium-high heat. Add bacon and cook until fat renders 2 to 3 minutes. Add the smashed garlic clove, thyme sprigs and Brussels sprouts and cook gently until slightly caramelized. Add stock and reduce heat to a simmer. Season with salt and a little pepper, cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes until tender. Remove lid and add a splash of vinegar and reduce until syrupy, 2 to 3 minutes.|After Brussels sprouts are done cooking, put them in oven safe dish. In sheet tray and toss bread crumbs with rosemary, thyme leaves and chopped garlic, then drizzle with a little olive oil and salt and pepper. Mais pour √™tre √† la mesure du moment, m√™me si nous n'avons pas de r√©sultats suffisamment d√©finis pour pouvoir les commenter utilement, voyons ce qui se pr√©sente. C'est une situation totalement inattendue, absolument inou√Øe. La d√©route du parti pr√©sidentiel est totale et aucune majorit√© ne se pr√©sente. Nous avons r√©ussi l'objectif politique que nous nous √©tions donn√© en moins d'un mois de faire tomber celui qui, avec autant d'arrogance, avait tordu le bras de tout le pays pour √™tre √©lu sans qu'on sache pour quoi faire.|La France s'est exprim√©e et il faut le dire, insuffisamment. Le niveau de l'abstention est encore beaucoup trop, ce qui signifie qu'une immense partie de la population ne sait de quel c√¥t√© se tourner. Tant et si bien que les trois blocs qui √©taient apparus √† la sortie de l'√©lection pr√©sidentielle continuent √† √™tre voisins dans des proportions quasi identiques. Sans que l'on sache √† cette heure si la perc√©e de la NUPES le place en premi√®re ou en deuxi√®me position. Mais c'est au total et avant tout l'√©chec √©lectoral de la macronie. C'est l'√©chec, plus grave, l'√©chec moral de ces gens qui donnaient des le√ßons √† tout le monde sans arr√™t et qui se pr√©tendaient le barrage √† l'extr√™me droite et qui auront ont eu pour principal r√©sultat d'en avoir renforc√© les rangs et sur 65 face √† face entre la Nupes et le Rassemblement national, les donneurs de le√ßons de la macronie ont √©t√© incapables de donner une consigne claire dans 52 cas. Ce qui les disqualifie, me semble t il dor√©navant, √† faire des le√ßons de morale pour qui que ce soit.|Quel bon d√©barras d'avoir vu apr√®s Monsieur Blanquer √©limin√© d√®s le premier tour, voire √©jecter l‚Äô√©borgneur Castaner et l‚Äôinjurieuse Montchalin. |Mon message ce soir, une fois de plus, est un message de combat. Des opportunit√©s incroyables vont se pr√©senter devant vous et en particulier devant vous la jeune g√©n√©ration qui √™tes celle qui appelle avec le plus de force √† la rupture avec ce monde et ses r√®gles d'organisation. Des opportunit√©s, parce que vous disposez d'un magnifique outil de combat dont vous aviez √©t√© priv√©s pendant tant de temps. Cet outil, c'est la Nupes. Ce sont ses parlementaires, ouvriers, ouvri√®res, salari√©s de tous ordres, de toutes les r√©gions de France, arrivant par dizaines sur les bancs de l'Assembl√©e nationale. Le Macronisme ne s'est pas seulement mis en faillite lui-m√™me, il a plong√© le pays dans une impasse.|Et tout √† l'heure, d√©j√†, nous avons entendu qu'il s'agissait de d√©passer les clivages. Il n'y a aucun clivage √† d√©passer avec nous parce que nous ne sommes pas du m√™me monde. Nous ne visons pas les m√™mes objectifs. Nous n'avons pas les m√™mes valeurs. Nous ne croyons pas au m√™me futur et comme nous pensons qu‚Äôils le savent. Alors, nous en concluons qu'ils se pr√©parent √† d'autres ententes, peut-√™tre.|Toujours est-il que si nous sommes √† la fin de la soir√©e, la Nupes, √† qui par diverses man≈ìuvres on a d√©j√† commenc√© par retirer quasiment 21 d√©put√©s des Outre-mer, et √† commencer par ceux de la R√©union ou six si√®ges sur sept sont emport√©s par des d√©put√©s qui voteront la confiance √† un gouvernement de la Nupes. Je veux vous dire que toutes les possibilit√©s sont dans vos mains.|Quant √† moi, je change de poste de combat, mais mon engagement est, demeurera, jusqu'√† mon dernier souffle, dans les premiers de vos rangs, si vous le voulez bien. Le grand jaillissement oui, le grand jaillissement de l'histoire du plus profond de ce qu'est la France des r√©bellions et des r√©volutions. Oui, ce grand jaillissement, dor√©navant, a un visage le visage de notre collectif, celui de l'Union populaire. Les d√©fis les plus inou√Øs vont s'accumuler devant vous. Que ce soit le changement climatique, que ce soit la grande crise financi√®re. Par quelque c√¥t√© que vous voyez ce monde finissant, c'est √† chaque fois des r√©ponses fulgurantes qu'il faudra apporter. Pas un instant, nous ne renoncerons √† l'ambition d'√™tre ceux qui gouvernent ce pays et qui l'am√®nent √† un autre horizon. Pas un instant, les salari√©s ne baisseront les bras. Pas un instant, les jeunes ne se diront fatigu√©s de la lutte. |Pour lire la suite du discours : https://melenchon.fr/2022/06/19/allocution-du-deuxieme-tour-des-elections-legislatives-de-la-nupes/

title: I'm Shipping My Shelby GT500 to the UK, FINALLY!
description: The time has arrived for my Shelby GT500 to go home! After owning the American Shmeemobile for 18 months, it is now the right moment to pack it up to send it to the UK and onwards to @The Shmuseum! Join me for the last drive in the USA and to send it on the way.|I tracked down my beastly Mustang on Auto Tempest at the start of 2021, took delivery of it at Ikonick Motors, then promptly installed SunTek Reaction PPF and fitted the Altered Black PPF stripes. It didn't take long to get on the road, before a 6 week adventure across the country all the way to LA with countless amazing stops and moments along the way. Since then, it has been based in Miami and popped up from time to time for various journeys, until this last month with the stops around New York before @Gumball 3000 brought us all the way back from Toronto to Miami.|Now though, with over 12,000 miles on the clock it is time to get it home at long last, to get the car dropped off for transport and all the registration with MyCarImport to get it onto UK soil and officially registered as SH67 MEE. For now that means cleaning it and preparing it for travel, with a few items boxed up including the spare wheels, and some other items to go through in due course.|However, before that, let's visit DuPontRegistry's new customer supercar experience for a soft preview of things to come and a look at some fantastic cars. The display includes a Lamborghini Sian Roadster, Essenza SC V12, a Porsche Carrera GT in Ferrari's Rosso Fuoco paint, an Aventador SVJ paint matched to the red sole of a Louboutin shoe, and plenty more.|It's then time for the road, and the very final drive in the USA, ensuring that the car is out of gas and ready for the sailing which will take 1-2 months to get to the UK, before the import process begins which in all will take about the same. I believe it should be 'good to go' somewhere around September, but let's see!|Thanks for watching, Tim|Chapters:|00:00 Intro|01:31 Preparing for Transport|04:41 Entering Supercar Heaven|06:13 DuPont Registry Experience|12:35 Washing the GT500|13:25 The Last Drive|23:06 Final Goodbye|25:24 Wrap Up|#Shelby #GT500 #DuPontRegistry|||Subscribe: http://bit.ly/Shmee150YT||Website: http://www.shmee150.com||Shop: http://shop.shmee150.com||Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/shmee150||Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/shmee150

title: Are They All The Same Motor Oil? Let's Settle This!  Four Levels of Pennzoil Motor Oil Compared
description: Let's find out if Pennzoil's motor oil (Pennzoil Synthetic Blend, Pennzoil Full Synthetic, Pennzoil Platinum and Pennzoil Ultra Platinum) are basically the oil.  All four oils tested sent to an independent oil lab for oil analysis. I tested oils for evaporative loss, lubricity or film strength, cold oil flow both new oil and after exposure to heat.  Additionally, in a final test, Pennzoil Ultra Platinum is exposed to 10% gasoline and another sample is exposed to antifreeze to see the impact it has on lubricity or oil performance.  I always buy all of the products tested to ensure unbiased test results. description: Top military officer said recruitment of soldiers will increase to over one lakh in the future under the Agnipath scheme. We've started small at 46,000 to analyse the scheme...and to build up infra capacity," said Additional Secretary Lt Gen Anil Puri, Department of Military Affairs (DMA). He asserted that ‚ÄòAgniveers‚Äô would get the same allowance in areas like Siachen which are applicable to regular soldiers. title: Tourists displace Ukrainian refugees in Bulgaria | Focus on Europe
description: Ukrainian refugees in Bulgaria have to vacate hotels in holiday regions. And there are difficulties with integration.|They fled from Ukraine: millions of people have been uprooted since the war begun. About 100.000 fled to Bulgaria, 60.000 of them were sheltering in hotels along the coastline of the Black Sea. But just ahead of the summer season, the government has been reducing compensation to hotel owners. Tens of thousands of refugees must be relocated within Bulgaria. Meanwhile the issue of Ukrainian refugees is increasingly polarising the country. title: Govt won't rollback 'Agnipath', says 'no place for arsonists in forces' amid widespread protests
description: The defence ministry has made its stand clear on the 'Agnipath' scheme. There will be no rollback despite raging protests across states. Top defence officials said that the reforms like Agnipath was long pending as the armed forces wanted to bring youthfulness and experience. It also warned the arsonists as protests over the scheme goes violent in several parts of the country. The Additional Secy of the Department for Military Affairs Lt.General Puri said that there is no space for indiscipline in the forces and aspirants have to pledge in enrollment form that they were not involved in arson. He further added that if during police verification, an FIR against the candidate is found then they simply can't join. Watch to know more.|#defenceministry #agnipath #agniveer #indianarmy #indiannavy #indianairforce #protest #agitation #recuitment #recruitmentscheme #modigovernment #modigovt #bihar #secundrabad

title: BREAKING: Hubble Just Made A Stunning Black Hole Discovery
description: While everyone's waiting for the first images of the James Webb Space Telescope, Hubble continues to make stunning astronomical discoveries. The Hubble Space Telescope has determined the mass of the first free-floating black hole in our Galaxy. The Milky Way is believed to be home to more than 100 million stellar-mass black holes. However, the problem is that since even light cannot escape the gravity of a black hole, it is impossible to discover them. So far, astronomers had only discovered black holes in binary systems by analyzing either the gravitational waves or electromagnetic radiation emitted when they feast on their companion stars.|But now, using the technique of gravitational microlensing and Hubble's meticulous observations, two teams of researchers have found the first evidence of a rogue black hole in our galaxy.|All Episodes Of The Series: https://bit.ly/369kG4p|Basics of Astrophysics series: https://bit.ly/3xII54M|REFERENCES:|Research Paper of the Berkeley Team: https://bit.ly/39CluAV|Research Paper of the  STScI Team: https://bit.ly/3bcoCUl|Earendel Episode of this series: https://bit.ly/3QsayXj|Roman Space Telescope: https://go.nasa.gov/3xAgfd3|Created By: Rishabh Nakra|Narrated By: Jeffrey Smith|The Secrets of the Universe on the internet:|Website: https://bit.ly/sou_website|Facebook: https://bit.ly/sou_fb|Instagram: https://bit.ly/sou_ig|Twitter: https://bit.ly/sou_twitter

title: How GM Is Going All In On Electrification | CNBC Marathon
description: CNBC Marathon revisits General Motors' shift into the electric vehicle market. |GM is one of the largest automakers in the world with a range of models falling under its four brands, Chevy, Buick, Cadillac, and GMC. The automaker made its name selling gas burning cars but in January 2021, it made a stunning announcement. The company said it ‚Äúaspires to eliminate tailpipe emissions from new light-duty vehicles by 2035.‚Äù This means that GM intends to stop selling gas-burning cars. General Motors says it wants to lead electric vehicle sales in North America by 2025, and vows that its new Ultium battery platform will drive that dominance.|Not only are cars going electric but so are boats. General Motors recently invested $150 million in one start-up, Pure Watercraft, to build an electric pontoon boat. title: The rise of a global company -  From the microscope to the moon landing | DW Documentary
description: 175 years ago, the young mechanic Carl Zeiss opened a small workshop for precision mechanics and optics. These humble beginnings in the German city of Jena were the foundation of the Zeiss technology company, which today operates worldwide.|The production of glass with game-changing optical properties was one of the developments that helped Carl Zeiss create a company that valued scientific research highly, while never forgetting science‚Äôs social impact. |Zeiss microscopes have been used by more than 30 Nobel Prize winners. To this day, these instruments offer unrivaled image resolution, with lenses that can display structures one thousand times smaller than a human hair. Light microscopes allow living cells to be examined with extreme gentleness and speed, as well.|The Zeiss company was involved in the moon landing in 1969, and thus helped redefine the limits of what humans are capable of. Images of the historic event were captured using Zeiss camera lenses developed specially for space. These lenses were key to the later development of photolithography, which plays a decisive role in the production of microchips. Developments in extreme ultraviolet lithography led to Zeiss winning the German Future Prize together with the Fraunhofer Institute and the Trumpf company.|#documentary #dwdocumentary |______|DW Documentary gives you knowledge beyond the headlines. title: Marcel the Shell With Shoes On: A tiny hero
description: When comedian-actor Jenny Slate and filmmaker Dean Fleischer-Camp created the voice of a tiny animated character ‚Äì a seashell with a googly eye, shoes, and a winning personality ‚Äì they could not predict that their quirky short films would become viral hits online, nor that the one-inch-tall shell would star in a feature-length movie, the heartwarming adventure "Marcel the Shell With Shoes On." Correspondent David Pogue talks with Slate and Fleischer-Camp about Marcel's sweet, funny quest to find his family; and with "60 Minutes" correspondent Lesley Stahl, who plays herself in the film.|"CBS Sunday Morning" features stories on the arts, music, nature, entertainment, sports, history, science and Americana, and highlights unique human accomplishments and achievements. title: Zelenskyy visits troops on Ukraine's southern front | DW News
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy has visited troops on the southern front line. title: OUR NEW HYBRID ELECTRIC CATAMARAN
description: This is the beginning of a very exciting journey!|‚ù§ Join Our Crew! ‚ù§ For exclusive content, behind the scenes & Q&A's: |http://bit.ly/patreon-wynn |https://www.gonewiththewynns.com/sailing |‚òùFull Scoop On The Blog|Full Disclosure:¬† Transparency is important to us because we want you to understand what our relationship with HH Catamarans means and how it will affect our content.¬† The short answer is, that it won't.¬† We did receive a small discount on the purchase of our boat in exchange for the publicity HH Catamarans will receive.¬† But HH fully agreed that it was important we retain full creative freedom and continue to create as we always have, by sharing our honest experiences.¬† It's because of this shared desire for transparency that we are very much looking forward to working with and owning an HH Catamaran.|üì∑ Photo & Video Gear üì∑|https://www.gonewiththewynns.com/photo-video-gear |üì± UPDATES on Social üì±  |INSTAGRAM: https://instagram.com/the_wynns/ |FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/GoneWithTheWynns |üìßEMAIL notifications, so you never miss a videoüç¶|http://bit.ly/gwtw-social|üé∂ MUSIC for vids. |2 Months Free:  https://bit.ly/artlist-GWTW|Artists ‚Äì Orkas|üé® Creative Assets for Vids (SFX, Templates & Presets): | - https://bit.ly/motion-array-GWTW |üéΩGET YOUR SWAG ON:  https://gonewiththewynns.teemill.com/|üíØFREE ways to support our productions|http://bit.ly/join-gwtw|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|WE‚ÄôRE JASON AND NIKKI WYNN.  A couple of modern-day documentarians, perpetual travelers, and seekers of tall tales.  |We‚Äôve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011. Why?  Because curiosity is the key to unlocking life.  It pushes us outside our comfort zone, softens our assumptions, and helps us embrace the great unknown.  The more we let our curiosity lead the way, the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us.|Our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land.  Self-reliance and living a sustainable lifestyle are a must.  It's all about managing our resources and we‚Äôre always looking for new and better ways to do so.  |We've lived off the grid for over 10 years now in everything from a Van to RV to a Sailboat. And over time we have learned a lot about renewable energy, creating safe drinking water, and managing our waste.|Our journey is ever-evolving but the mission remains the same: #CultivateCuriosity|Timestamps if you like to Jump Around:|00:00 OUR NEXT SAILBOAT REVEALED|02:54 Why We're Buying an HH44|03:45 Parallel Hybrid Electric Engines ECO-DRIVE|05:32 Insanely Large Lithium Battery Bank|06:29 Largest Solar Array of ANY Production Catamaran|08:11 Build Quality - CARBON FIBER & Epoxy Resins |08:32 Easy to Sail & Clean Decks|09:07 Performance Sailing & POLARS|09:36 Amazing Cockpit Design|10:26 Salon, All-Electric Galley & Forward Facing Nav|11:45 Cabins, Hulls, Workshop & Pantry|12:30 Our Next Plans & Delivery|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|#BoatLife #Catamaran #TravelVlog #DigitalNomad #LifeStyle #Sailboats |¬© Gone With the Wynns 2022

title: He saved stone barn. Also built unreal villa under hillside
description: Gorka Ibargoyen bought an abandoned stone housebarn in the Bera Valley of Navarra and wanted to expand it to fit large gatherings without destroying the original character. With the help of architect friend Jordi Hidalgo Tan√© he went underground, building an annex to the primary home inside the adjacent hillside. Accessible via an all-glass corridor the addition is nearly invisible.|The cave-like addition resembles a fissure in a mountain, and that is what inspired Tan√©‚Äôs design, and is nearly invisible from the outside: it is accessible via a transparent, all-glass corridor. When looking at the model, Ibargoyen feared the hidden home might resemble a bunker, but the glass skylight in the green roof light combined with the long window running down the entire length of the structure brings in plenty of daylight to the subterranean shelter.|To unify the two structures, the used only glass, concrete, and wood for the interior, resulting in a concrete sink and a wooden shower. While the result is modern elegance, Ibargoyen insists it‚Äôs not a fussy home ‚ÄúThings are made to be used, and to show wear over time‚Äù, he explains and pointing to a wine stain on the cement countertop, he adds, ‚ÄúThat is happiness‚Äù.|https://www.landaburuborda.com/|On *faircompanies https://faircompanies.com/videos/he-saved-stone-barn-also-built-unreal-villa-under-hillside/
